ğŸ“ Problem Statement

Halsey receives a string S containing only X and Y.
An ideal string must alternate between X and Y.

She can remove characters one by one.
Find the minimum number of removals required.

ğŸ”¢ Input Specification

input1: String S

ğŸ¯ Output Specification

Return the number of removals

ğŸ’¡ Approach

Traverse the string

If two adjacent characters are the same â†’ removal needed

Count such occurrences

ğŸ’» Java Code
import java.util.Scanner;

public class IdealString {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        String S = sc.next();
        int removals = 0;

        for (int i = 1; i < S.length(); i++) {
            if (S.charAt(i) == S.charAt(i - 1)) {
                removals++;
            }
        }

        System.out.println(removals);
        sc.close();
    }
}

ğŸ§ª Sample Input
XYXXXY

âœ… Output

2
2
